snippet.textDisplay:
Honestly, this right here, is why I would never want to be a professional strongman. You have no time for anything except eat, train, shit, sleep, repeat. You pretty much live like an animal almost.
Humans are not optimized to become giants. Actually nothing is really, elephants, whales, all these other animals they essentially need to eat constantly, the bigger something gets, the more energy it requires to just exist. As you put on more and more size for strength, it takes more and more to maintain it, until a person reaches their own physical ceiling of how much their body can maintain.


Plus, you eat so much food that you just become desensitized to it, like Eddie says, it becomes a chore...just about every strong man will say the same, it's like a 24/7 mukbang, you eat until you can eat no more. And honestly, I'm a person who likes my food, so I prefer to keep it that way just to be honest. XD
